cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is about text infilling, which is a natural language generation task. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper proposes an iterative inference algorithm based on gradient search, which is a machine learning optimization technique. This suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper uses neural sequence generative models, which are a type of artificial intelligence, indicating that it could also fit into cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The proposed method is also based on optimization, which is a common theme in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates its method on text infilling tasks with different mask strategies, which could be related to computer vision and image inpainting, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
